<ns2191:section xmlns:ns2191="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.integration.introduction.introduction">
  <ns2192:title xmlns:ns2192="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Introduction</ns2192:title>
  <ns2193:para xmlns:ns2193="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Larger enterprises usually employ a range of systems using a range of technologies. 
    Business processes need to be realized accross these systems and to this end these
    systems need to be seemlessly integrated.
  </ns2193:para>
  
  <ns2194:section xmlns:ns2194="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns2195:title xmlns:ns2195="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Integration support as part of infrastructure layer</ns2195:title>
    <ns2196:para xmlns:ns2196="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      Within a layered architecture the integration support is usually provided within the
      infrastructure layer. This layer may provide a <ns2197:emphasis xmlns:ns2197="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">message bus</ns2197:emphasis>
      supporting a standard infrastructure for organization-wide integration.
    </ns2196:para>
  </ns2194:section>
</ns2191:section>